title: Grateful Dead Live at Alpine Valley Music Theatre on 1989-07-17
lineage: Master Cassettes (Maxell MX 100) Tascam 112MKII -> Korg MR-1, 1bit 2.8MHz -> USB -> Korg Audio Gate Software 24bit 96KHz -> Wave Lab 6.0 w/UAD -> R8brain for 16bit 44.1KHz sample rate conversion -> Traders Little Helper flac 8 -> Tagged w/Tag & Rename
description: Set 1 Let The Good Times Roll, Feel Like A Stranger, Built To Last, Me & My Uncle-> Cumberland Blues, It's All Over Now, Row Jimmy, When I Paint My Masterpiece, When Push Comes To Shove, The Music Never Stopped Set 2 China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band-> Standing On the Moon*, Drums, Jam-> The Wheel-> Gimme Some Lovin'-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Not Fade Away, E: We Bid You Good Night, E: Johnny B. Goode *with a full moon rising behind the band; material from this show is featured in the video Downhill from Here.

reviews.review_text: a good clean run! Zero noise reduction was applied.

yes siree this ones a good one and no, no NR was applied..the phasing you hear is the fact of the repeater stacks and the house sound..the delay is added for the lawn crowd so its "in synch", but the mics will pic up a faint echo of fob sound...

**__**

Bid You Goodnight Tease? I never understand why people call the end of Goin' Down The Road a We Bid You Goodnight Tease. It is just part of Goin' Down The Road the way the Dead played it. It is NOT We Bid You Goodnight and it is certainly not the exact same melody, just close.
